      "writtenOn": "2017-05-26T20:40:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If t.Run(....) calls the passed function in a separate go-routines then you will most likely only see the last value of the tests map being tested.   Even if you know for sure that t.Run(..) is executed synchronously this should be avoided. \nInstead wrap the call to t.Run in a closure where you pass the value of the loop variable:\nfor .... {\n   func(c testcase) {\n      t.Run(....)\n   }(c)\n}",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 96,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 99,
        "endChar": 4
      },
      "revId": "2ec381e5c9ed4371699714566f85cf8c9d122c81",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
